endDate.description: The end date of the listing.

lastTransactionCreateDate.description: The date the data was created.

lastTransactionID.description: The last transaction ID of the listing.

pageNo.description: The page number of the listing.

pageSize.description: The page size of the listing.

nextUrl.description: The next url of the listing.

streetNumber.description: The street number portion of a listed property's street address.  In some areas the street number may contain non-numeric characters.  This field can also contain extensions and modifiers to the street number, such as "1/2" or "-B".  This street number field should not include Prefixes, Direction or Suffixes.

streetPrefix.description: The direction indicator that precedes the listed property's street name.

streetName.description: The street name and suffix portion of a listed property's street address. This field should not include Prefixes or Direction.

streetDirection.description: The direction indicator that follows a listed property's street address.

streetAddress.description: The full street address including unit number. Does not include city, state, or postal code.

stateProvince.description: Text field containing the accepted postal abbreviation for the state or province.

postalCode.description: The postal code portion of a street or mailing address.

county.description: The County, Parish or other regional authority

sqFt.description: The total square footage of the lot.  This field is related to the Lot Size Area and Lot Size Units and must be in sync with the values represented in those fields.  Lot Size Source also applies to this field when used.

apn.description: An Assessor Parcel Number (APN) is a unique number assigned to each parcel of land by a county tax assessor.

beds.description: The total number of bedrooms in a residential property.

totalBaths.description: The total number of bathrooms in a residential property.

latitude.description: The geographic latitude of some reference point on the property, specified in degrees and decimal parts.  Positive numbers must not include the plus symbol.

longitude.description: The geographic longitude of some reference point on the property, specified in degrees and decimal parts. Positive numbers must not include the plus symbol.

unitNumber.description: Text field containing the number or portion of a larger building or complex. Unit Number should appear following the street suffix or, if it exists, the street suffix direction, in the street address. Examples are: "APT G", "55", etc.

floor.description: A numeric field that describes the level within the structure, SFR or a unit in a building, where the main entry to the dwelling is located.  When a unit has one floor it is implicit that this is also the level of the unit itself.

propertyType.description: A list of types of properties such as Residential, Lease, Income, Land, Mobile, Commercial Sale, etc...

numberOfStructures.description: The total number of structures on the property.

lotWidthFeet.description: Lot width is the horizontal distance between the side lot lines, measured at right angles to the lot depth at a point midway between the front and rear lot lines.

lotDepthFeet.description: Lot depth is the distance between the front and rear lot lines, measured at right angles to the lot width at a point midway between the side lot lines.

lotSizeFeet.description: The total square footage of the lot.  This field is related to the Lot Size Area and Lot Size Units and must be in sync with the values represented in those fields.  Lot Size Source also applies to this field when used.

lotSizeAcres.description: The total Acres of the lot.  This field is related to the Lot Size Area and Lot Size Units and must be in sync with the values represented in those fields.  Lot Size Source also applies to this field when used.

boatFacility.description: Boat Facility is a feature of the property that allows for the storage of a boat.

parkingDescription.description: Type of Parking available for the property.

numberOfParkingSpaces.description: The total number of parking spaces available for the property.

pool.description: The pool feature of the property.

viewType.description: The view type of the property. (e.g. Gulf, Bay, Mountain, etc...)

hoa.description: The home owner association of the property.

hoaFeesMonthly.description: The monthly HOA fees of the property.

community.description: A list of features related to, or available within, the community.

subdivision.description: A neighborhood, community, complex or builder tract.

schoolDistrict.description: The school district of the property.

structureType.description: The type of structure that the property completely or partially encompasses.  For example, House or Cabin are the overall structure and typically sold or leased as a whole.  Multi Family and Docks may be sold in whole, but are often sold or leased by unit/slip.  This field is the type of structure as opposed to style, which is under the Architectural Style field.

structureWidth.description: The structure width of the property.

structureDepth.description: The structure depth of the property.

structureFireplaceCount.description: The structure fireplace count of the property.

structureRoomCount.description: The structure room count of the property.

structureStories.description: The structure stories of the property.

yearBuilt.description: The structure year built of the property.

transactionStatus.description: The status of the listing as it reflects the state of the contract between the listing agent and seller or an agreement with a buyer (Active, Active Under Contract, Canceled, Closed, Expired, Pending, Withdrawn).

originalListDate.description: Original list date of the property.

originalListPrice.description: Original list price of the property.

originalListSource.description: The original list source of the property.

date.description: The transactional date automatically recorded by the MLS system representing the date the listing was last modified.

mlsName.description: The multiple listing service name of the property.

mlsListingNumber.description: The well known identifier for the listing. The value may be identical to that of the Listing Key, but the Listing ID is intended to be the value used by a human to retrieve the information about a specific listing. In a multiple originating system or a merged system, this value may not be unique and may require the use of the provider system to create a synthetic unique value.

listingBroker.description: The listing broker of the property.

listingBrokerEmail.description: The listing broker email of the property.

specialCircumstance.description: The special circumstance of the property.

transactionRemarks.description: The transaction remarks of the property.

agencyID.description: The agency ID of the agent.

requestor.description: The name of user, who registered this request.
